%% Feast Operator - Data Flow Diagram
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist
    participant RHODS as rhods-operator
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Operator as Feast Operator<br/>Controller Manager
    participant Online as Online Store<br/>6566/TCP HTTP | 6567/TCP HTTPS
    participant Offline as Offline Store<br/>8815/TCP HTTP | 8816/TCP HTTPS
    participant Registry as Registry Server<br/>6570/TCP gRPC | 6572/TCP REST
    participant DB as External DB<br/>(Snowflake/Cassandra/SQL)
    participant Notebook as Kubeflow Notebook
    participant CronJob as CronJob Pod

    Note over RHODS,Operator: Flow 1: Feature Store Deployment
    RHODS->>K8sAPI: Deploy feast-operator<br/>Kustomize overlay
    K8sAPI->>Operator: Create Deployment
    User->>K8sAPI: Create FeatureStore CR
    K8sAPI->>Operator: Watch event
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Deployments, Services,<br/>ConfigMaps, PVCs, ServiceAccounts
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: Resources created

    Note over User,Online: Flow 2: Online Feature Serving
    User->>Online: GET/POST features<br/>HTTP/HTTPS 80/443<br/>Auth: K8s RBAC / OIDC
    Online->>DB: Query features<br/>Secret credentials
    DB-->>Online: Feature data
    Online-->>User: Feature response

    Note over CronJob,Operator: Flow 3: CronJob Materialization
    CronJob->>K8sAPI: kubectl exec<br/>443/TCP HTTPS<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI->>Online: exec into pod
    Online->>Online: feast apply /<br/>materialize-incremental

    Note over Notebook,Operator: Flow 4: Notebook Integration
    User->>K8sAPI: Add feast label to Notebook CR
    K8sAPI->>Operator: NotebookConfigMapReconciler<br/>watch event
    Operator->>K8sAPI: List FeatureStores,<br/>Create ConfigMap
    K8sAPI-->>Notebook: Mount feast config ConfigMap
